    • Method Detail

      • getCohortName

        java.lang.String getCohortName(DicomObject currentObject,
                             DicomObject cachedObject)
        Get the name of the cohort to which the current object belongs.
        Parameters:
        currentObject - the object that has madve it down the pipeline to the calling stage.
        cachedObject - the object that was cached at the head end of the pipe.
        Returns:
        the name of the cohort to which the objects belong.

      • connect

        Status connect()
        Connect to the external logging database. This method is called whenever the exporter starts a sequence of exports. It is not called again until the exporter empties the export queue, disconnects, and then receives another QueueEntry to export.
        Returns:
        Status.OK or Status.FAIL

      • disconnect

        Status disconnect()
        Disconnect from the external logging database. This method is called when the exporter empties the export queue or when the pipeline tells the stage to shut down. This method should commit the database and then disconnect.
        Returns:
        Status.OK or Status.FAIL

      • export

        Status export(QueueEntry queueEntry)
        Export one QueueEntry to the external logging database. This method is called from the exporter thread.
        Returns:
        Status.OK, Status.RETRY, or Status.FAIL
